  <statement>
      <p>
          A psychologist wants to know the probability that exposure to a certain simuli increases anxiety.  He wants to find a <m> 95</m>% confidence interval with margin of error <m>ME=0.02</m>.
      </p>
      <p>
          A previous study showed that  of <m>46\ </m> test subjects,  <m>20\ </m>had increased anxiety after exposure to the stimuli.  How many subjects should now be tested to obtain a <m>95</m>% confidence interval with margin of error <m>ME=0.02</m>?
      </p>
      
