  <answer>
      <title>Partial Solution:</title>
      <ul>
          <li>
              The sample proportion of the initial study is <m>\hat{p}=0.43478260869565216</m>.
          </li>
          <li>
              For a 95% confidence interval,  <m>z^*=1.9599639845400536</m>.
          </li>
          <li>
              The margin of error is <m>ME=0.02</m>.
          </li>
          <li>
              The number of subjects should now be tested is at least <m>2361</m>.
          </li>
      </ul>
          
      
  </answer>
